##I sell cell phones in Wuhan

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

Author | Yu Fan

Editor | Wei Jia

It was the traditional peak season for the mobile phone industry, and distributors and retailers across the country were gearing up years ago to get a jump on sales, but an epidemic hit everyone.

According to a report from Tianfeng securities, shipments of mobile phones in China will fall by 50% to 60% during the 2020 spring festival compared with the same period last year, resulting in the current high level of 50-60 million units in mobile phone stocks.

The mobile phone industry is also essentially a retail industry, in the face of the epidemic, the size of the mobile phone brand stores had to close temporarily to avoid risk. Apple, for example, had only 80 percent of its 42 stores in mainland China as of Feb. 29. Another factor that affects mobile phone sales is logistics. Data shows that the overall resumption rate of major express enterprises is about 66.7% .

IDC, a research firm, predicts that the domestic market as a whole will face a sharp drop of about 40% from January to February 2020 compared with the same period last year, and that the overall market will gradually enter a recovery period within March if the epidemic is brought under stable control, but it is still struggling to return to the level of the same period last year. The domestic market is expected to suffer a year-on-year decline of more than 30 per cent through the first quarter.

The number of these changes and the impact behind them would be magnified even further in Wuhan.

On January 24, the day after the city was closed, the Wuhan Xiaomi home announced that it would suspend the distribution and installation of household appliances in the city, and that the distribution of small goods in the city continued. However, the head of Xiaomi's home in Hubei told Caijing that due to the special situation in Hubei, Wuhan currently can not be distributed in the same city, and other mobile phone brands are also in a similar situation. A number of mobile phone brand agents in Wuhan also confirmed the news to Caijing.

Wuhan seems to be "frozen" , but enterprises to resume work, students to resume classes, working from home, online classes of the student party, need mobile phones. Wuhan around the medical team members, mobile phones every day through the disinfection process, very easy to damage, they have a large number of maintenance, exchange needs. A number of Wuhan residents told Caijing, although express delivery is returning to work, but the reality is that e-commerce platform has not shown Wuhan delivery.

The bottom of the market has become a last resort for shopkeepers, four of whom were interviewed by Caijing, a campus Internet celebrity who started out as a mobile phone promoter, and volunteers who moved ten million protective supplies to the front line, there are county in Hubei Province for the dealers, as well as the last century into the business operator agent.

They in Wuhan "closed city" to continue to operate, but also the first to feel the cold, offline closure shop, cash flow taut, years ago, the hoarding of goods are stacked in the warehouse, can not be turned into cash, can only wait.

No matter how hard the phone tries, it's already at a dead end

To lay out smart homes

Ren Aihua, founder of Hubei Aihua Communication

We are offline Huawei authorized experience store, mainly in retail, in Wuhan, all 20 direct stores opened in the mall. The company has been mainly offline, but the outbreak of the outbreak, but also congratulated themselves from more than a year ago began to raise the developer team, burned a lot of money, the development of their own mall, customers in this outbreak are from the online mall orders. We finally want to ERP financial system, billing system, membership system all open, now in continuous optimization, has not yet fully online.

Over the past year, the company's sales of more than 600 million, if there is no epidemic, I believe at least a month to sell more than 10,000 units, and this month only about 1,000 units.

The real feeling of the outbreak came three days before the city was closed. I contacted my friend in Shandong and sent 10,000 double national standard KN95 masks to Wuhan. The original plan was to send a mask to every customer arriving at the shop. Unexpectedly, Wuhan closed the city, logistics out of the problem, all the people began to look for me to buy masks, I learned that Wuhan hospitals are short of medical supplies, at that time decided to donate all to the hospital.

A lot of people are still looking for me, so what do I do? I go around buying. From January 21 to the present, we have purchased more than one million protective materials out of our own pocket, and ten million of them have been donated by our friends from other places.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Edward Ren is carrying 84 sterile water

Source / interviewee

A friend in Taizhou, Zhejiang Province, said he would donate 100 million yuan. I told him that there was no shortage of money here. He collected 100,000 masks, 10 tons of 84 disinfectant, and 10,000 goggles. It was early February, and no one dared to come to Wuhan. He took out 50,000 yuan and asked people to load up the supplies and set out for Wuhan in the middle of the night. Before setting out, the driver's Teacher's child did not agree: "must go to Wuhan, run over from me" , can only unload all the material car. Three days later, I asked other friends to help me deliver the goods to Wuhan.

My wife and I have formed a volunteer team, and many Wuhan entrepreneurs have joined us. The team is to raise medical supplies from all over the country and send them to hospitals and communities in Wuhan.

The staff of Vulcan Mountain, Concord Hospital, Tongji Hospital, Jinyintan hospital and medical teams around the world need smart screens, tablet computers, mobile phones and Smart Stereos. As long as we have them in stock, they will be sent to us as soon as possible, to make it easier for health care workers to receive data. Some of it was donated by us, and some of it was paid for.

A lot of people advised me to promote the experience in the first line, the store where the mall is also in contact with me, said that as long as speak out, how much inventory is not a problem, I did not agree.

Inventory pressure is indeed very big, 50 million years ago to store up inventory, Wuhan people can only work from home, home classes, can not go out consumption, we do community group purchase and Douyin live, express delivery can not guarantee the time limit, small partners on home delivery. In order to clear the stock, we continue this month special sale, gifts are also many, N95 protective masks, protective clothing.

Some of the team in particular do not understand the small partner, feel "you do not make money, but also let the company's people risk their lives to deliver goods. ". It's really dangerous out there, there are six of us who haven't had a day off in a month, in addition to delivering protective equipment and delivering goods to clients, every one of them is on the move, I'm under a lot of psychological pressure, but as a Wuhan native myself, I really want to contribute to the customer in this way.

At the moment of the epidemic, frankly speaking, the first thing to worry about is survival, not business. There is too much suffering around me. I am lucky not to be infected. I simply do not have enough energy to think about the problems of the enterprise. All I want is the epidemic to end quickly, so we can get back to our normal lives, and as far as the company is concerned, when this epidemic is over, we can start over.

Edward Yam is carrying supplies, provided by the source / interviewee

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This year is my 21st year, from 1999 began selling BP, to Phs, 2g, 3G, 4g to 5G, every era has experienced. I've been focused on Huawei since 2010, when my friends ran off with my money. I started bringing Huawei to the top shopping centers in Wuhan when people said I was crazy and they all made multiple brands.

When the brand started hard, you did not accompany, when it flourished, you want to share, it is impossible. Along the way, my experience is, to see a brand, do fine, and can not only do the phone, how much power the phone, also has to the bottleneck, the future or layout of smart home, this is a market to be developed.

When business is good, there's no time to collect

Now there's time for repairs

Du Min, the cell phone dealer

Our store in central China Communications Plaza opened 14 years, mainly to wholesale, mainly for the county in Hubei Province dealers. Sales are dominated by mobile phones, other tablets, laptops are also sold, the brand is dominated by apple and Huawei.

OPPO and Vivo have an extremely strict area protection system, with the same requirements for each distributor, and the exclusive stores now available on the market are sold at the official guided prices. Huawei is sold because, this brand in Hubei Province, the better source of goods, although there are regional protection restrictions, but does not affect our sales to Hubei Province. Apple's products are available anywhere in the country, with no restrictions. It used to carry niche brands, Meizu, ZTE, Nubia, and then it lost money and slowly stopped buying.

Relatively speaking, the mobile phone industry price transparency, low profits, but because the price base is large, it is easy to be misunderstood by some retail customers, increased a lot of communication costs. We control the dealer, the profit is thinner, the circulation needs to be faster, a batch of goods in an average of two days to sell out, otherwise it will lose money.

Eighty-five percent of the store's business is with regular customers, and another 15 percent is with strangers. Since 2018, there have been fewer and fewer new customers, and business has been getting harder every year. Last year, production fell by a fifth. My dealer's business is even worse, and now more than half of them have switched careers.

I started selling used mobile phones in 2018 and found that they were very popular. The market is not as competitive as the new machines, and there is room for profit. In the best years of the year, when HTC and apple sold fourth and sixth generation phones for more than a day's pay, there was now time for used phones, as well as the repair business of changing batteries and screens.

Image / visual China

Wuhan City this month, our colleagues can only stay at home to send a friend circle, tell others "I still have goods" , "can be delivered with the city. Now most people in Wuhan are more rational, can not buy things certainly do not buy, must buy things to consider buying, although there are old customers looking for me to get goods, now a day also sell 6-8 mobile phones. Below the county dealers also begged me to deliver, but the goods are sealed in the shop can not take out, and logistics, and I can give them the delivery time, the home of the only stock has long been sold out.

The prices of mobile phones in Wuhan are a little higher than usual. First, the only ones that are in circulation are those that were stockpiled years ago, which are not cheap in themselves. Second, during special periods, everyone has difficulties, and it is acceptable for some urgent customers to earn a little more. Because students in Wuhan can only take classes online, and presumably for a long time, parents believe that mobile phones are bad for their children's eyes, and demand for tablets has risen. The original 3,000 Yuan Apple IPAD now costs 3,500 yuan. But the mobile phone industry and other industries, Wuhan once the whole city open, two or three days later, as long as the goods from other provinces come in, the price will soon return to normal.

For us, it is impossible to talk about making money, just barely, and the business is doing less day by day. Now there are business, because e-commerce platform not to Wuhan delivery, they can only find trust with the city to get goods, wait for e-commerce platform normal delivery, most people will give us up. In addition, the market shop probably can not open for business, even if allowed to open, may only the need for mobile phone maintenance in the last few days blowout, the demand is short-lived. By then, the store's inventory will finally be available, and the customer will be gone.

Now I just have to keep taking orders

Liquidate the family's inventory

The owner of becks digital store

After the closure of the city, I should still be active in the streets of Wuhan one of the people, not in the delivery, or in the City Express Mail on the road.

Because of the epidemic, there is now an increase in equipment leasing. First because of one of my old customers, he is a first-line medical staff, mobile phones are sterilized every day, water, contact me to repair. I don't think we should give him the phone for free just because it's affecting the work of the staff, and we agreed that when the outbreak was over, he would call me to fix it.

Later, the medical rescue teams around Wuhan, I think they are unfamiliar with life, cell phone broken no place to repair, also can not buy new, I rent equipment for free to them.

I got into mobile first because of HTC. In 2011, I came to Wuhan to study as a freshman while working as an HTC campus agent. At that time, part of the motivation was to earn some pocket money, but more to let others affirm themselves, especially girls, so they mixed in the forums, micro-blogs, QQ space, promote themselves.

That year there was a movie called Love Is Not Blind. At the height of its popularity, I planned a "33 days of free film pasting" campaign in the campus store and was interviewed by the media. At the time, I didn't take it seriously. A few days later, my cell phone messages exploded, it turns out that I have been reported by the media as a typical college student to earn his own living. I've been getting calls from more and more people, and I've graduated from a part-time job to being an HTC smart consultant. Think about it now, that early in the year to do on-line and off-line linkage marketing, put themselves first into the campus "little internet celebrities" , then talk about business.

Junior year, listen to the seniors said rental is very hard, every move is a history of blood and tears, I consider buying a house in Wuhan, so as not to rent after graduation. Occasionally, I went to see a house with a colleague, he did not buy, I bought the building's largest size. I was 20 years old, and with $200,000 in family support and my own savings, I closed a one million deal and, of course, started paying off my mortgage.

My mobile phone business from the beginning to rent a section of small counters, to co-management of a shop, and finally opened their own style of digital shop, I was really rooted in Wuhan. Also during that time, because riding an electric bike to the customer delivery cold many times, so go to the Audi store to buy the A6L, that is life's first car. Later often listen to small partner talk about Porsche more cattle, finally in last year a sports car dream. I mean, the novelty's worn off, the car's mostly in the garage, but it's a treat after all these years.

I started with mobile phones on campus, and my customers were mainly students. Later, many old customers joined the work and recommended me to the company. There are more and more enterprise-level customers, such as Betta fish and some real estate companies, i opened a third chain store in my office building. If we want to make money, we need to help our customers to solve the problem of diversification, purchase the products of the annual meeting, and even the demand of wine. The demand of individual customers is also diverse, although the mobile phone is a home-watching product, but notebook computers, desktops, cameras, and even drones, dyson series products, as long as the digital life of technology-related products, we sell.

When I started in 2011, stores were hard to find, and people were pouring in. Last year, the entire mobile phone market fell sharply, regardless of the off-season peak season, month and month are off-season, some of the same industry closure, some of the transfer line. Because I pay attention to online marketing 9 years ago, each store also has the exclusive customer group, the scope of business is also wide, we 89% of the orders are online find, last year overall stable rise.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source / interviewee

The first month after the Spring Festival every year is the most important month in the first half of our store. Students Start School, enterprises recruit new staff, it is always the need to buy a lot of new equipment waiting for us, don't even think about it now. Most worrying is that years ago, the stock of goods in the shop can not come out, but also to pay car loans, housing loans, cash flow can not bear.

The most important thing in our business is not necessarily to make money, but to keep the cash flow flowing, so now we have to keep taking orders and liquidate our family's inventory. If we run out of stock, we can transfer it from our local counterparts, even if the cost is higher, we have to stay in business.

I don't think I'M GONNA make it to 5G

Considering a career change after the outbreak

Hou Fuan, China Mobile Agent

I am an agent of the nature of business hall, shops in Wuhan are street-facing, from state contractors, provincial contractors to take goods, mainly relying on China Mobile's subsidy policies, such as the charge to send mobile phones, mobile phones and other consumer insurance. Huawei, for example, can participate in these activities if a Huawei model is shortlisted in the carrier library.

At the beginning of the industry, when the mobile phone industry was just emerging in the last century, I felt that I had entered a once-in-a-millennium industry, sitting in the shop every day waiting for customers.

But as operators'market space has been compressed, the once favorable policies for users have been gradually disappearing since 2017, especially with the rise of e-commerce platforms, including the major brands that have followed the trend to build their own online stores, the impact on our stores, which don't have a price advantage, can be fatal. We have to go out and find business, such as doing discount activities in the community.

In fact, our store has paid great attention to online maintenance, usually customers to do business, buy mobile phones, will remain Wechat, usually will maintain. Starting in 2019, it was clear to me that the industry was already struggling, with sales falling 30-50 per cent a year.

Image / visual China

Years ago, I took out 700,000 pressure goods, who knows Wuhan suddenly closed, store blockade, stock can not take out, a small number of people through wechat contact me to buy mobile phones, but logistics can not be delivered, only with the city people meat delivery. This time last year, 500,600 cell phones a month, and after the lockdown, orders were in the single digits.

Personally, I think it's scary to go out now. Even if the epidemic ends, everyone in Wuhan will have a shadow in their hearts. Everyone still feels that it's safest to stay at home. It may not be until August or September that the behavior of going out and spending money will resume, even then, the number of people touching the store must be very small. This year it's only online, but most of us don't have the pricing advantage or the customer base to sell online.

I and a few colleagues are more pessimistic about the market this year, the epidemic will shuffle a large number of small and medium-sized stores, but only mom and pop stores can survive. I can't do anything right now, I just have to wait. I've been watching the news lately, trying to figure out a better way to interact with my regular customers, but the results haven't been as good as I'd hoped, so if there's something to be happy about, that's when the landlord calls, asking for some rent relief.

This year, I have been in business for 20 years, experienced 3G, 4g switch tide, 5g judgment is that, although the state support, but within a year there is no large-scale switch demand. I might not make it to the next switchboard, and after the outbreak, I'm thinking about switching.
